unction: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ws_getsInvisible Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Defines the behavior of the worksheet plug-in component when another worksheet is selected and the current worksheet becomes invisible. Explain this code operation getsInvisible ; Your code here end; operation getsInvisible Copy Description The operation is optional. Example The following operation sends a message to the Messages tab by calling the IDE API operation outputMessage . Explain this code operation ws_getsInVisible activate \"IDE_API_1\".outputMessage(\"Worksheet Gets InVisible (instance=%%$instancename)\") if ($procerror != 0) putmess \"Activate error: %%$procerror%%%, %%$procerrorcontext%%%\" endif end ; ws_getsInVisible Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}